This paper deals with natural language generation from structured data, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) research. The proposed model uses attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in NLP and machine learning (ML) research. The focus on tables and their structure suggests a potential overlap with database (DB) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DB (Databases).
